President Barack Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key administration posts. Glyn Davies, a career member of the Senior Foreign Service, was nominated as the United States Representative to the Vienna Office of the United Nations and the International Atomic Energy Agency. Jim R. Esquea, an analyst for Income Security and Medicaid for the Democratic staff of the Senate Budget Committee, was nominated as Assistant Secretary for Legislation in the Department of Health and Human Services. Jonathan B. Jarvis, who has been an employee of the National Park Service for over 30 years, was nominated as the Director of the National Park Service in the Department of the Interior. President Obama expressed confidence in these individuals and their ability to tackle important challenges such as health reform, national security, and strengthening the economy.